question_text: Have you eaten at least 5 servings of fruit and vegetables at day? (1 serving = 103 g * 5= 515)
At least 3 servings of those F&V you ate at day were vegetables? (1 serving 89.2*3=268)
Have you eaten less than 1/2 cup of patatoes at day?
Have you eaten 5 or less servings of cereals at day? (1 serving = 34.5 g of bread or 75.3 g of pasta/rice, 1 serving of cereals= 55g)
At least half of the servings of cereals you ate were whole grain?
Have you eaten 4 serving of legumes per week? (1 serving = 82.5 per day, 82.4 times 4= 330 per week= 47 g per day)
Have you eaten 3 servings of nuts per week?  (1 serving = 30 g, 30 times 3 = 90 gramos per week, 13 g per day)
Have you eaten 3 servings of fish and seafood per week? (1 serving = 132 g, 132 times 3= 396 per week, 57 g per day)
Out of the servings of fish, were they mostly oily fish?
Have you eaten 4 eggs per week? (1 egg=50 g, 50 times 4 = 200 per week, 29 g per day)
Have you eaten less than 2 servings of cheese, yogurt or fermented milk? (1 serving = 109 g of fresh cheese, 56 g hard cheese, 170 g of yogurt, 1 serving of dairy = 112 g, 112 times 2 = 224)
Have you eaten < of 3 serving of meat per week? (1 serving = 113.2 g, 113,2 times 3 = 340 per week, 49 per day)
Of those servings, were at least half of them white meat from poultry?
Have you eaten 1 serving of processed meat per week? (1 serving=42.8 g per week, 6 g per day)
Have you used olive oil for cooking and food dressing?
Have you eaten < of 1 serving of sweets, chocolates, cookies, industrial bakery, and snacks per week? (1 serving = 51,2 per week, 7 g per day)
Have you added salt at table?
Did you drink 2 liter of water (8 glasses) per day? (8*237g= 1896 g (2litrs))
Did you drink 1 glass of low-fat milk per day? (245 ml)
Did you drink 1 cup of coffee or tea per day? (237 mL)
Did you drink 1 glass of whole-fat milk per day? (245 ml)
Did you drink 1 glass of fruit juice per day? (248 ml)
Did you drink 1 can of low calorie beverages per day? (370 mL)
Did you drink 1 can of carbonated beverages per day? (370 mL)
Did you drink more than 1 alcoholic drink (if women) or more than 2 (if men) per day? (1 drink is 147 ml of wine, 356 ml of beer or 42 ml of liquors)
